What would happen if I add essential oils to this humidifier? Essential oils will corrode the humidifier, causing the water tank or base to crack. Could I put the humidifier on the floor or a wooden table? Yes, but it isn’t the smartest move: 1. Best place to put a humidifier is where the most airflow is. 2. Potential of wetting the surroundings due to locally high humidity levels, it is recommended to put a tray underneath it. Is the bubbling/knocking sound it makes while running normally? It is normal for the humidifier to have bubbling sounds sometimes. It is the sound of water moving from the water tank to the base. Other times it is quiet and does not affect its performance. Can I use tap water or is distilled water preferred? It depends on where you live. In some areas, water is richer in minerals. The humidifier won’t instantly go haywire if you do use tap water, but in the long term will cause scale and you need to maintain it more often. Distilled water is recommended. Is it normal to have standing water in the base when you refill the water reservoir? Yes, it's normal. The water flowing from the tank to the base when you add water and place it back is part of the humidifier's operation. It draws water from the tank and disperses it through the base to increase room humidity.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Simple, but Effective
reviews.reviewText: I got this to deal with dry air while I sleep. It works quite well, very quiet and can dump quite a bit of moisture. To function it needs a hard base that won't obstruct air intake. The nozzle on top can be rotated to aim in a particular direction, but you're warned not to place the unit on wood or aimed at a surface that won't tolerate steam. I placed on my bathroom counter. Downside? While it can be aimed somewhat, and you have four levels of output volume, there is no set point for humidity - I wish it had that feature, but the price point likely rules our having a sensor and attendant control display.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Elevate Comfort in Your Bedroom and Nursery
reviews.reviewText: The Rosekm Cool Mist Humidifier has become an indispensable addition to my bedroom, helping me create the perfect environment for restful sleep, healthy plants, and a comfortable nursery for my baby. This small yet powerful ultrasonic humidifier has proven to be an outstanding choice for elevating indoor air quality.The standout feature of this humidifier is its 2.0L capacity, which is perfectly suited for bedroom use. Whether you're looking to improve the humidity in your sleeping space, provide a nurturing environment for your indoor plants, or maintain an optimal atmosphere for your baby's nursery, this humidifier has you covered.The 360° nozzle is a game-changer, allowing you to direct the cool mist precisely where it's needed. It ensures even distribution of humidity, preventing dry spots in the room and providing the comfort you desire.The Rosekm Cool Mist Humidifier operates with an ultrasonic system, which means it's incredibly quiet. This makes it an ideal choice for bedroom use, ensuring that it won't disrupt your sleep or your baby's peaceful rest.The auto shut-off feature adds an extra layer of convenience and safety. When the water level is low, the humidifier will automatically turn off, preventing any damage to the device and ensuring its long-term durability.The filterless design is a major plus, as it reduces the ongoing maintenance and cost associated with filter replacement. Simply fill the tank with water, and you're good to go.The sleek black color of the humidifier adds a touch of modernity to your room, making it a stylish and functional addition to your bedroom, nursery, or any other living space.In conclusion, the Rosekm Cool Mist Humidifier is a top-tier choice for anyone seeking a small yet powerful solution to improve air quality and comfort in their bedroom, nursery, or other living areas. Its 2.0L capacity, 360° nozzle, quiet operation, and auto shut-off feature make it a versatile and reliable humidifier. I highly recommend the Rosekm Cool Mist Humidifier to those looking to enhance their indoor environment and create a healthier, more comfortable space. It's a true asset to any room.
